WEBVTT

00:00:00.570 --> 00:00:03.381
Mohamed El-Erian: It terrified me,
absolutely terrified me.

00:00:03.405 --> 00:00:04.676
And it still terrifies me.

00:00:04.700 --> 00:00:07.204
Adam Grant: Mohamed El-Erian
is an economist.

00:00:07.228 --> 00:00:10.126
And he gets a lot of requests
to speak in public.

00:00:10.150 --> 00:00:11.912
ME: No matter how often I do it,

00:00:11.936 --> 00:00:13.836
the night before, I will not sleep.

00:00:13.860 --> 00:00:15.745
AG: What is it that you're afraid of?

00:00:15.769 --> 00:00:20.706
ME: I'm worried about not being able
to put a coherent sentence in place.

00:00:20.730 --> 00:00:23.556
I'm still worried about it right now
as I'm talking to you.

00:00:23.580 --> 00:00:24.758
AG: (Laughs)

00:00:24.782 --> 00:00:28.079
Last year, he was asked to give
a speech about the global economy

